This paper is primarily focused on social choice theory, which falls under the category of cs.GT (Computer Science - Game Theory). The paper also involves metrics and distances, which suggests a possible fit for cs.DS (Computer Science - Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of different voting rules, which could be relevant to cs.AI (Computer Science - Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Computer Science - Machine Learning). Finally, the paper introduces a new metric for evaluating social choice rules, which could be relevant to cs.SI (Computer Science - Social and Information Networks).
